<div id="review_1065389713" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1065389713" />
    <a title="Patrick McCoy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/678506-patrick-mccoy"><img alt="Patrick McCoy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1420614390p2/678506.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1065389713?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patrick McCoy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patrick McCoy" href="/user/show/678506-patrick-mccoy">Patrick McCoy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/678506-patrick-mccoy?shelf=biography-autobiography">biography-autobiography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/678506-patrick-mccoy?shelf=criticism">criticism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/678506-patrick-mccoy?shelf=japan">japan</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1065389713" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8261960166712039354">I was inspired to read Marguerite Yourcenar&apos;s book, Mishima: A Vision Of The Void (1980) because of eminent Japanese critic Donald Richie&apos;s praise of it. Make no mistake, Yourcenar has not attempted to write a definitive biography or critical study, however, has drafted a tribute to Japanese author Yukio Mishima as a symbol in life as well as expressed in his writings. She has made some interesting observations about his actions in life and how they reflected his ideas that have been preserved i</span>
  <span id="freeText8261960166712039354" style="display:none">I was inspired to read Marguerite Yourcenar's book, Mishima: A Vision Of The Void (1980) because of eminent Japanese critic Donald Richie's praise of it. Make no mistake, Yourcenar has not attempted to write a definitive biography or critical study, however, has drafted a tribute to Japanese author Yukio Mishima as a symbol in life as well as expressed in his writings. She has made some interesting observations about his actions in life and how they reflected his ideas that have been preserved in his body of writing. I suppose this would be of most interest to people who are well-versed in the life and work of Mishima.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8261960166712039354" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


